name: Cursive Binary: What I’ve created has never existed. [After Enheduanna; study for a painting.]
description: NEAR-FUTURE TRANSLATIONS. Translation of a line attributed to the world’s first known human poet, Enheduanna (2285-2250 BCE), into Cursive Binary, a proposed language for transhuman communication. By @sashastiles, as part of an ongoing project to preserve the earliest traces of human imagination for future readers. sashastiles.com
